ata/testimonials.json` with 8-10 placeholder testimonials\n   572→3. All text translated in i18n files\n   573→\n   574→**Validate:**\n   575→- [ ] Testimonials render in all 3 languages\n   576→- [ ] Cards display correctly with ratings\n   577→- [ ] Responsive grid layout\n   578→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(pages): T9 — testimonials page`\n   579→\n   580→---\n   581→\n   582→### - [ ] T9b: Build Events/Updates Page with Subscription Mechanism\n   583→\n   584→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V2\n   585→\n   586→**Knowledge Base:**\n   587→- User requirement: \"daily updates where users can subscribe to them\"\n   588→- WhatsApp broadcast and newsletter patterns\n   589→\n   590→**Do:**\n   591→1. Create `src/pages/[lang]/events.astro`:\n   592→   - Upcoming events section (pujas, yagnas, workshops, speaking engagements)\n   593→   - Latest updates / news feed (festival predictions, planetary transits, eclipse alerts)\n   594→   - Past events gallery with photos\n   595→   - Event cards with date, title, description, location, CTA\n   596→2. Create subscription mechanism:\n   597→   - Email subscription form (integrate with free tier: Buttondown, Mailchimp, or ConvertKit)\n   598→   - WhatsApp broadcast opt-in link (wa.me link with \"Subscribe\" prefilled message)\n   599→   - \"Get Daily Predictions\" CTA\n   600→3. Create `src/data/events.json` with 4-6 placeholder events\n   601→4. Create `src/components/sections/EventCard.astro`\n   602→5. Create `src/components/sections/SubscribeSection.astro` — reusable on homepage + events page\n   603→6. All text in translation files for 3 languages\n   604→\n   605→**Validate:**\n   606→- [ ] Events page renders in all 3 languages\n   607→- [ ] Event cards display date, title, description properly\n   608→- [ ] Subscription form captures email\n   609→- [ ] WhatsApp subscribe link works\n   610→- [ ] SubscribeSection reusable on homepage\n   611→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(pages): T9b — events/updates page with subscription`\n   612→\n   613→---\n   614→\n   615→### - [ ] T9c: Build 404 Page and Privacy Policy Page (DPDP Act Compliant)\n   616→\n   617→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V2\n   618→\n   619→**Knowledge Base:**\n   620→- India's Digital Personal Data Protection Act (DPDP) 2023 + DPDP Rules 2025\n   621→- DPDP requires: explicit cookie consent (opt-in), clear privacy notice, data principal rights\n   622→- Full enforcement by May 2027, but best to comply now\n   623→\n   624→**Do:**\n   625→1. Create `src/pages/[lang]/404.astro`:\n   626→   - Themed 404 with celestial/cosmic design (\"Lost in the Stars?\")\n   627→   - Search suggestions\n   628→   - Links to popular pages (Home, Services, Contact)\n   629→   - Translated for all 3 languages\n   630→2. Create `src/pages/[lang]/privacy-policy.astro`:\n   631→   - What personal data is collected (form submissions, analytics)\n   632→   - Purpose of processing\n   633→   - Cookie usage disclosure\n   634→   - Data principal rights (access, correction, erasure, grievance)\n   635→   - Contact details for data-related requests\n   636→   - Available in all 3 languages (DPDP requires notices in scheduled languages)\n   637→3. Create simple cookie consent banner component:\n   638→   - `src/components/layout/CookieConsent.astro`\n   639→   - Opt-in model (no cookies before consent)\n   640→   - \"Accept\" / \"Decline\" buttons\n   641→   - Links to privacy policy\n   642→   - Remembers choice in localStorage\n   643→4. Add privacy policy link to footer on all pages\n   644→\n   645→**Validate:**\n   646→- [ ] 404 page renders in all 3 languages with correct links\n   647→- [ ] Privacy policy is comprehensive and DPDP-compliant\n   648→- [ ] Cookie consent banner appears on first visit\n   649→- [ ] Analytics only load after consent\n   650→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(pages): T9c — 404 page, privacy policy, cookie consent`\n   651→\n   652→---\n   653→\n   654→### - [ ] V3: Gate — Verify All Pages Render Correctly\n   655→\n   656→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T4, T5, T6, T7, T8, T9, T9b, T9c\n   657→\n   658→**Checks:**\n   659→- [ ] All pages render in `/en/`, `/hi/`, `/gu/` without errors\n   660→- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds with no warnings\n   661→- [ ] Navigation between all pages works\n   662→- [ ] Responsive on mobile (375px), tablet (768px), desktop (1440px)\n   663→- [ ] All CTAs link correctly\n   664→- [ ] Accessibility: semantic HTML, alt text, keyboard navigation\n   665→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-3 + VFX-3 in Appendix\n   666→\n   667→---\n   668→\n   669→## PHASE 5 — Content Creation & Translation\n   670→\n   671→### - [ ] T10: Write English Content for All 12 Service Pages\n   672→\n   673→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** R2\n   674→\n   675→**Knowledge Base:**\n   676→- R2 service content research report\n   677→- Content JSON schema from T6\n   678→- Astrologer's actual service descriptions\n   679→\n   680→**Do:**\n   681→1. Write comprehensive English content for each service:\n   682→   - Title and subtitle\n   683→   - 300-500 word introduction\n   684→   - 6-8 benefits\n   685→   - 4-6 process steps\n   686→   - 8-10 FAQs with detailed answers\n   687→   - SEO meta title, description, keywords\n   688→   - Related services mapping\n   689→2. Save as JSON files at `src/content/services/en/{slug}.json`\n   690→3. Ensure content is authoritative, trustworthy, SEO-rich\n   691→4. Include relevant vedic/spiritual context for each service\n   692→\n   693→**Validate:**\n   694→- [ ] All 12 service content files created\n   695→- [ ] Each has introduction, benefits, process, FAQs, SEO\n   696→- [ ] Content is professional and culturally appropriate\n   697→- [ ] Keywords are naturally integrated\n   698→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(content): T10 — English content for 12 services`\n   699→\n   700→---\n   701→\n   702→### - [ ] T11: Translate All Con