**Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T11, T12, T14\n   794→\n   795→**Checks:**\n   796→- [ ] All service pages load content in all 3 languages\n   797→- [ ] All blog posts render in all 3 languages\n   798→- [ ] No missing translation keys (compare en.json keys vs hi.json and gu.json)\n   799→- [ ] Hindi and Gujarati text renders with correct fonts\n   800→- [ ] SEO meta tags present in all languages\n   801→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-4 + VFX-4 in Appendix\n   802→\n   803→---\n   804→\n   805→## PHASE 6 — SEO Optimization\n   806→\n   807→### - [ ] T15: Implement SEO — Schema Markup, Meta Tags, Sitemap, Hreflang\n   808→\n   809→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V3\n   810→\n   811→**Do:**\n   812→1. Create `src/components/SEOHead.astro`:\n   813→   - Dynamic meta title and description per page/language\n   814→   - hreflang tags for all 3 languages + x-default\n   815→   - Canonical URLs\n   816→   - Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:locale)\n   817→   - Twitter card tags\n   818→2. Add JSON-LD structured data:\n   819→   - LocalBusiness schema (astrologer practice)\n   820→   - Person schema (Pandit Mahadev Joshi)\n   821→   - Service schema (for each service page)\n   822→   - Article schema (for blog posts)\n   823→   - BreadcrumbList schema\n   824→   - FAQPage schema (for service FAQs)\n   825→3. Create `public/robots.txt` with sitemap reference\n   826→4. Configure `@astrojs/sitemap` with i18n hreflang in astro.config\n   827→5. Add breadcrumbs component with schema markup\n   828→\n   829→**Validate:**\n   830→- [ ] All pages have unique meta titles and descriptions per language\n   831→- [ ] hreflang tags present on every page for all 3 languages\n   832→- [ ] JSON-LD validates at schema.org validator\n   833→- [ ] Sitemap generates with correct URLs\n   834→- [ ] robots.txt is accessible\n   835→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(seo): T15 — schema markup, meta tags, sitemap, hreflang`\n   836→\n   837→---\n   838→\n   839→### - [ ] T16: Add Analytics, Structured Data, Open Graph\n   840→\n   841→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** T15\n   842→\n   843→**Do:**\n   844→1. Create `src/components/AnalyticsHead.astro`:\n   845→   - Google Analytics 4 placeholder (configurable tag ID)\n   846→   - Google Tag Manager placeholder\n   847→   - Plausible Analytics placeholder (privacy-friendly alternative)\n   848→2. Ensure Open Graph images are set per page\n   849→3. Add social media preview optimization\n   850→4. Create `src/data/seo-keywords.json` — keyword mapping per service per language\n   851→5. Internal linking strategy: service pages → related blogs → related services\n   852→\n   853→**Validate:**\n   854→- [ ] Analytics scripts load in production build only\n   855→- [ ] OG tags render correctly (test with og:image validator)\n   856→- [ ] Social sharing generates correct previews\n   857→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(seo): T16 — analytics and Open Graph optimization`\n   858→\n   859→---\n   860→\n   861→### - [ ] T17: Create JustDial & Google My Business Optimization Guide\n   862→\n   863→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** T15\n   864→\n   865→**Do:**\n   866→1. Create `.tasks/mahi-astro/reports/T17-local-seo-guide.html` — Zen HTML report:\n   867→   - Google Business Profile setup guide with exact steps\n   868→   - JustDial listing optimization guide\n   869→   - NAP consistency checklist\n   870→   - Review collection strategy\n   871→   - Google Posts content calendar template\n   872→   - Local citation building list (Sulekha, IndiaMART, etc.)\n   873→   - Social media profile setup checklist\n   874→2. Add UTM tracking parameters for JustDial/GMB links\n   875→3. Create a `public/.well-known/` directory for domain verification if needed\n   876→\n   877→**Validate:**\n   878→- [ ] Guide is comprehensive and actionable\n   879→- [ ] Includes specific steps for both JustDial and GMB\n   880→- [ ] UTM parameters documented\n   881→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(seo): T17 — JustDial and GMB optimization guide`\n   882→\n   883→---\n   884→\n   885→### - [ ] V5: Gate — Verify SEO Implementation\n   886→\n   887→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T16, T17\n   888→\n   889→**Checks:**\n   890→- [ ] Run Lighthouse SEO audit — target 90+ score\n   891→- [ ] Validate JSON-LD at validator.schema.org\n   892→- [ ] Verify sitemap.xml has all pages in all languages\n   893→- [ ] Verify hreflang consistency\n   894→- [ ] Check meta tags on 5 random pages\n   895→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-5 + VFX-5 in Appendix\n   896→\n   897→---\n   898→\n   899→## PHASE 7 — Visual Polish & Images\n   900→\n   901→### - [ ] T18: Source and Place Hero Images, Icons, Decorative Elements\n   902→\n   903→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V3\n   904→\n   905→**Knowledge Base:**\n   906→- R3 report (image requirements and sources)\n   907→\n   908→**Do:**\n   909→1. Download free high-quality images from Unsplash/Pexels:\n   910→   - Homepage hero: cosmic/celestial theme\n   911→   - About page: spiritual/meditation background\n   912→   - Service-specific images (chakras, gemstones, vastu, kundli, etc.)\n   913→   - Blog featured images\n   914→2. Create SVG icons for:\n   915→   - 12 zodiac signs\n   916→   - Service icons (kundli, vastu, gemstone, chakra, mantra, etc.)\n   917→   - Decorative mandalas and borders\n   918→3. Place images in `public/images/` organized by section\n   919→4. Add placeholder for astrologer profile photo\n   920→5. Update all components to reference actual images\n   921→\n   922→**Validate:**\n   923→- [ ] All hero images placed and rendering\n   924→- [ ] Icons display correctly at multiple sizes\n   925→- [ ] No broken image references\n   926→- [ ] Images are appropriately themed (Hindu/spiritual/astrology)\n   927→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(images): T18 — hero images, icons, decorative elements`\n   928→\n   929→---\n   930→\n   931→### - [ ] T19: Optimize All Images (WebP, Lazy Loading, Responsive)\n   932→\n   933→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** T18\n   934→\n   935→**Do:**\n   936→1. Install `@astrojs/image` or use Astro's built-in `<Image>` component\n   937→2. Convert all images to WebP format with fallbacks\n   938→3. Implement responsive `srcset` for different viewport sizes\n   939→4. Add lazy loading to below-fold images\n   940→5. Optimize SVG icons (SVGO)\n   941→6. Ensure hero images have `fetchpriority=\"high\"` and `loading=\"eager\"`\n   942→7. Add proper alt text to all images (translated per language)\n   943→\n   944→**Validate:**\n   945→- [ ] All images serve WebP where supported\n   946→- [ ] Lazy loading works for below-fold images\n   947→- [ ] Alt text present on all images in correct language\n   948→- [ ] Total image payload under 500KB for initial page load\n   949→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(images): T19 — image optimization, WebP, lazy loading`\n   950→\n   951→---\n   952→\n   953→### - [ ] V6: Gate — Verify Visual Assets & Performance\n   954→\n   955→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T19\n   956→\n   957→**Checks:**\n   958→- [ ] Lighthouse Performance score 90+\n   959→- [ ] No broken images on any page\n   960→- [ ] Images responsive at all breakpoints\n   961→- [ ] Alt text present and translated\n   962→- [ ] Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1\n   963→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-6 + VFX-6 in Appendix\n   964→\n   965→---\n   966→\n   967→## PHASE 8 — End-to-End Testing\n   968→\n   969→### - [ ] T20: Write Playwright E2E Tests\n   970→\n   971→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V4, V5, V6\n   972→\n   973→**Do:**\n   974→1. Install and configure Playwright: `npm init playwright@latest`\n   975→2. Create test suites:\n   976→   - `tests/navigation.spec.ts` — test all nav links, language switching, breadcrumbs\n   977→   - `tests/homepage.spec.ts` — hero renders, services grid, CTAs work, testimonials\n   978→   - `tests/services.spec.ts` — all 12 service pages load, FAQ accordion, related services\n   979→   - `tests/blog.spec.ts` — blog listing, individual post, category filter\n   980→   - `tests/contact.spec.ts` — form fields present, WhatsApp link, phone link\n   981→   - `tests/i18n.spec.ts` — language switching preserves page, correct content loads\n   982→   - `tests/seo.spec.ts` — meta tags, hreflang, schema markup present\n   983→   - `tests/responsive.spec.ts` — mobile, tablet, desktop layouts\n   984→   - `tests/accessibility.spec.ts` — axe-core audit, keyboard nav, ARIA\n   985→3. Each test covers all 3 languages\n   986→4. Include visual regression snapshots for key pages\n   987→\n   988→**Validate:**\n   989→- [ ] All test files created\n   990→- [ ] Tests run and pass: `npx playwright test`\n   991→- [ ] Coverage: navigation, i18n, services, blog, contact, SEO, responsive, a11y\n   992→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(tests): T20 — Playwright E2E test suite`\n   993→\n   994→---\n   995→\n   996→### - [ ] V7: Gate — All Tests Pass\n   997→\n   998→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T20\n   999→\n  1000→**Checks:**\n  1001→- [ ] `npx playwright test` — 100% pass rate\n  1002→- [ ] No flaky tests\n  1003→- [ ] Build succeeds: `npm run build`\n  1004→- [ ] If tests fail → create FX-7 + VFX-7 in Appendix\n  1005→\n  1006→---\n  1007→\n  1008→## PHASE 9 — Deployment\n  1009→\n  1010→### - [ ] T21: Initialize GitHub Repository\n  1011→\n  1012→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V7\n  1013→\n  1014→**Do:**\n  1015→1. Create `.gitignore` (node_modules, .astro, dist, .env, .tasks/)\n  1016→2. Initialize git repo: `git init`\n  1017→3. Create initial commit with all code\n  1018→4. Create GitHub repo via `gh repo create belive-astrology --public`\n  1019→5. Push to GitHub\n  1020→6. Add README.md with project overview, setup, and deployment instructions\n  1021→\n  1022→**Validate:**\n  1023→- [ ] GitHub repo created and accessible\n  1024→- [ ] All code pushed\n  1025→- [ ] README explains setup and development\n  1026→- [ ] Git commit: `chore(deploy): T21 — GitHub repository initialized`\n  1027→\n  1028→---\n  1029→\n  1030→### - [ ] T22: Deploy to Vercel\n  1031→\n  1032→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** T21\n  1033→\n  1034→**Do:**\n  1035→1. Install Vercel CLI: `npm i -g vercel`\n  1036→2. Run `vercel` to link project\n  1037→3. Configure build settings:\n  1038→   - Framework: Astro\n  1039→   - Build command: `npm run build`\n  1040→   - Output: `dist/`\n  1041→4. Deploy: `vercel --prod`\n  1042→5. Verify all pages load on production URL\n  1043→6. Document deployment URL and settings\n  1044→\n  1045→**Validate:**\n  1046→- [ ] Site deploys successfully to Vercel\n  1047→- [ ] All pages accessible on production URL\n  1048→- [ ] All 3 languages work on production\n  1049→- [ ] No console errors\n  1050→- [ ] Git commit: `chore(deploy): T22 — deployed to Vercel`\n  1051→\n  1052→---\n  1053→\n  1054→### - [ ] V8: Gate — Final Production Verification\n  1055→\n  1056→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T22\n  1057→\n  1058→**Checks:**\n  1059→- [ ] All pages load on production URL in all 3 languages\n  1060→- [ ] Lighthouse scores: Performance 90+, SEO 90+, Accessibility 90+, Best Practices 90+\n  1061→- [ ] Mobile responsive on real devices (or emulator)\n  1062→- [ ] WhatsApp/phone links work\n  1063→- [ ] Contact form submits correctly\n  1064→- [ ] Sitemap accessible at /sitemap-index.xml\n  1065→- [ ] robots.txt accessible\n  1066→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-8 + VFX-8 in Appendix\n  1067→\n  1068→---\n  1069→\n  1070→## PHASE 10 — CMS Integration (Post-Deploy)\n  1071→\n  1072→### - [ ] T23: Integrate Keystatic CMS — Full Content Management\n  1073→\n  1074→**Type:** Build | **Model:** claude-opus-4-6 | **Depends on:** V8\n  1075→\n  1076→**Knowledge Base:**\n  1077→- Keystatic — open source, Git-based CMS with visual editor, TypeScript support\n  1078→- Official Astro integration: https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/cms/keystatic/\n  1079→- Free: stores content as Markdown/JSON in Git repo (no database, no paid service)\n  1080→- Works on Vercel free tier — admin panel at /keystatic route\n  1081→- **Why Keystatic:** fully free, TypeScript-native, GitHub App auto-setup, clean admin UI, works with Astro + Vercel\n  1082→\n  1083→**Do:**\n  1084→1. Install Keystatic: `npm install @keystatic/core @keystatic/astro`\n  1085→2. Configure `keystatic.config.ts` with ALL content collections:\n  1086→   - **Blogs** → `src/content/blog/{lang}/` — title, excerpt, content (rich text), category, tags, hero image, SEO meta\n  1087→   - **Events** → `src/data/events.json` — title, date, description, location, type (puja/workshop/talk), image\n  1088→   - **Testimonials** → `src/data/testimonials.json` — client name, city, service, rating, text, date\n  1089→   - **Services** → `src/content/services/{lang}/` — all service fields (intro, benefits, FAQs, process, SEO)\n  1090→   - **i18n strings** → `src/content/i18n/{lang}.json` — editable UI text (nav labels, CTAs, footer, headings)\n  1091→   - **Site Config** → `src/data/site-config.ts` — contact info, social links, astrologer bio (singleton)\n  1092→3. Add Keystatic integration to `astro.config.mjs` (hybrid mode for /keystatic route)\n  1093→4. Set up GitHub App for Keystatic (automated setup wizard)\n  1094→5. Configure admin panel at `/keystatic` route\n  1095→6. Test each collection: create → edit → delete → verify renders on site\n  1096→7. Create `docs/cms-guide.md` — plain language guide for the astrologer:\n  1097→   - How to log in (GitHub account)\n  1098→   - How to create a blog post with images\n  1099→   - How to add/edit events\n  1100→   - How to manage testimonials\n  1101→   - How to update service descriptions\n  1102→   - How to edit navigation text and CTAs\n  1103→   - How changes go live (save → auto-deploy → 30 seconds)\n  1104→\n  1105→**Validate:**\n  1106→- [ ] `/keystatic` admin panel loads on production\n  1107→- [ ] Blog CRUD: create post → appears on site after Vercel deploy\n  1108→- [ ] Events CRUD: add event → shows on events page\n  1109→- [ ] Testimonials CRUD: add testimonial → shows on testimonials page and homepage\n  1110→- [ ] Services: edit service description → updated on service page\n  1111→- [ ] i18n: edit nav label → updated across site\n  1112→- [ ] Content saves to Git repo correctly\n  1113→- [ ] CMS guide complete and easy to follow\n  1114→- [ ] Git commit: `feat(cms): T23 — Keystatic CMS for all content management`\n  1115→\n  1116→---\n  1117→\n  1118→### - [ ] V9: Gate — Verify CMS Functionality\n  1119→\n  1120→**Type:** Verification | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** T23\n  1121→\n  1122→**Checks:**\n  1123→- [ ] Admin panel accessible and functional on production\n  1124→- [ ] All 6 collections editable (blogs, events, testimonials, services, i18n, site config)\n  1125→- [ ] Content appears on site after save + deploy\n  1126→- [ ] No regressions on existing pages\n  1127→- [ ] Vercel hybrid mode works (static pages + /keystatic SSR)\n  1128→- [ ] CMS guide is clear enough for non-technical user\n  1129→- [ ] If issues found → create FX-9 + VFX-9 in Appendix\n  1130→\n  1131→---\n  1132→\n  1133→## APPENDIX — Fix Tasks\n  1134→\n  1135→_Fix tasks will be created here by verification gates as issues are discovered._\n  1136→\n  1137→### Template:\n  1138→\n  1139→```\n  1140→### - [ ] FX-N: Fix [Issue Description]\n  1141→**Type:** Fix | **Model:** claude-sonnet-4-6 | **Depends on:** V[X]\n  1142→**Error:** [Exact error or issue]\n  1143→**Root Cause:** [Analysis]\n  1144→**Fix:**\n  1145→1. Step-by-step fix instructions\n  1146→**Validate:**\n  1147→- [ ] Issue resolved\n  1148→- [ ] No regressions\n  1149→- [ ] Git commit: `fix(scope): FX-N — description`\n  1150→```\n  1151→\n  1152→---\n  1153→\n  1154→## Booking System Recommendations (Post-Launch)\n  1155→\n  1156→### Recommended Architecture:\n  1157→1. **Primary:** WhatsApp Business link (`wa.me/918154992727?text=...`) — floating button + hero CTA\n  1158→2. **Secondary:** Cal.com or Calendly embedded booking page (for international clients, Google Calendar sync)\n  1159→3. **Automation:** WhatsApp Business API (via WappBiz or Twilio) for:\n  1160→   - Booking confirmations\n  1161→   - Appointment reminders (24hr before)\n  1162→   - Birth detail collection form\n  1163→4. **Notifications:** Google Calendar integration for astrologer's schedule management\n  1164→5. **CRM:** Simple Google Sheets integration for client records (via Zapier/Make)\n  1165→\n  1166→### Future Enhancements:\n  1167→- Online payment integration (Razorpay for India, Stripe for US)\n  1168→- Client portal with consultation history\n  1169→- Daily/weekly horoscope subscription (email + WhatsApp broadcast)\n  1170→- Free Kundli generator tool (drives organic traffic)\n  1171→","numLines":1171,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1171}}}
